(@p__linq__0 datetime2(7),@p__linq__1 datetime2(7))SELECT       [Project1].[Id] AS [Id],       [Project1].[OrderDate] AS [OrderDate],       [Project1].[TotalAmount] AS [TotalAmount],       [Project1].[CustomerId] AS [CustomerId],       [Project1].[Id1] AS [Id1],       [Project1].[Name] AS [Name],       [Project1].[Email] AS [Email],       [Project1].[CreatedDate] AS [CreatedDate],       [Project1].[C1] AS [C1],       [Project1].[Id2] AS [Id2],       [Project1].[Quantity] AS [Quantity],       [Project1].[Price] AS [Price],       [Project1].[OrderId] AS [OrderId],       [Project1].[ProductId] AS [ProductId]      FROM ( SELECT           [Extent1].[Id] AS [Id],           [Extent1].[OrderDate] AS [OrderDate],           [Extent1].[TotalAmount] AS [TotalAmount],           [Extent1].[CustomerId] AS [CustomerId],           [Extent2].[Id] AS [Id1],           [Extent2].[Name] AS [Name],           [Extent2].[Email] AS [Email],           [Extent2].[CreatedDate] AS [CreatedDate],           [Extent3].[Id] AS [Id2],           [Extent3].[Quantity] AS [Quantity],           [Extent3].[Price] AS [Price],           [Extent3].[OrderId] AS [OrderId],           [Extent3].[ProductId] AS [ProductId],           CASE WHEN ([Extent3].[Id] IS NULL) THEN CAST(NULL AS int) ELSE 1 END AS [C1]          FROM   [dbo].[Order] AS [Extent1]          INNER JOIN [dbo].[Customer] AS [Extent2] ON [Extent1].[CustomerId] = [Extent2].[Id]          LEFT OUTER JOIN [dbo].[OrderItem] AS [Extent3] ON [Extent1].[Id] = [Extent3].[OrderId]          WHERE ([Extent1].[OrderDate] >= @p__linq__0) AND ([Extent1].[OrderDate] <= @p__linq__1)      )  AS [Project1]      ORDER BY [Project1].[OrderDate] ASC, [Project1].[Id] ASC, [Project1].[Id1] ASC, [Project1].[C1] ASC
